{"comments":"Pie/Donut Chart Module\n\nProvides pure geometric calculations for pie charts and minimal FFI\nfor browser-only operations (animations, explode effects, tooltips).\n\n## Pure Functions (No FFI)\n\n- `findSliceAtAngle` — Find which pie slice contains a given angle\n- `normalizeAngle` — Normalize angle to [0, 2π) range\n- `angleInRange` — Check if angle falls within slice bounds\n- `computeSliceAngles` — Calculate start/end angles from values\n\n## Browser Boundaries (FFI Required)\n\n- Slice animations (scale/rotate transforms)\n- Explode effects (translate transforms)\n- Tooltip display (DOM creation/positioning)\n- Hover highlights (filter/opacity manipulation)\n- Mouse angle calculation (getBoundingClientRect)\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Angular bounds of a pie slice\n\nAll angles are in radians, measured from the positive X-axis,\ngoing counter-clockwise (standard mathematical convention).\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["startAngle",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["endAngle",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[94,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[91,1]},"title":"SliceAngles"},{"children":[],"comments":"Data for a pie slice including computed values\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["label",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["value",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["percentage",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[101,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[97,1]},"title":"SliceData"},{"children":[],"comments":"Result of finding a slice at an angle\n\nReturns -1 if no slice contains the angle (shouldn't happen\nwith properly formed pie charts covering the full circle).\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["index",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["slice",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Chart","PieChart"],"SliceAngles"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[110,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[107,1]},"title":"SliceAtAngleResult"},{"children":[],"comments":"Find which slice contains the given angle\n\nThis is a pure function — no DOM access required.\nThe angle should be in radians.\n\n## Algorithm\n\n1. Normalize the input angle to [0, 2π)\n2. Normalize each slice's start/end angles\n3. Find the first slice where angle falls within bounds\n\n## Example\n\n```purescript\nlet slices = \n      [ { startAngle: 0.0, endAngle: pi / 2.0 }     -- 0° to 90°\n      , { startAngle: pi / 2.0, endAngle: pi }      -- 90° to 180°\n      , { startAngle: pi, endAngle: 2.0 * pi }      -- 180° to 360°\n      ]\n    result = findSliceAtAngle slices (pi / 4.0)\n-- result.index == 0 (first slice contains 45°)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Chart","PieChart"],"SliceAngles"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Chart","PieChart"],"SliceAtAngleResult"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[171,70],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[171,1]},"title":"findSliceAtAngle"},{"children":[],"comments":"Normalize an angle to the range [0, 2π)\n\nThis handles negative angles and angles > 2π by wrapping them\ninto the standard range.\n\n## Examples\n\n```purescript\nnormalizeAngle (-pi)     -- π (wraps around)\nnormalizeAngle (3.0 * pi) -- π (3π mod 2π = π)\nnormalizeAngle 0.5       -- 0.5 (already in range)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[128,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[128,1]},"title":"normalizeAngle"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if an angle falls within a slice's angular bounds\n\nHandles the case where the slice crosses the 0/2π boundary.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Chart","PieChart"],"SliceAngles"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[140,49],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[140,1]},"title":"angleInRange"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute slice angles from raw values\n\nGiven an array of numeric values, computes the start and end\nangles for each slice of a pie chart.\n\n## Example\n\n```purescript\nlet values = [25.0, 25.0, 50.0]\n    angles = computeSliceAngles values\n-- angles[0] = { startAngle: 0, endAngle: π/2 }       (25%)\n-- angles[1] = { startAngle: π/2, endAngle: π }       (25%)\n-- angles[2] = { startAngle: π, endAngle: 2π }        (50%)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Chart","PieChart"],"SliceAngles"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[205,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Chart/PieChart.purs","start":[205,1]},"title":"computeSliceAngles"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute percentages from raw values\n\nUseful for tooltip display and labels.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":